HEADWORD: Pismire
<hw>Pis"mire</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Piss</ets> +
<ets>mire</ets>; so called because it discharges a moisture vulgarly
considered urine. See <er>Mire</er> an ant.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An ant, or emmet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

